01:00:49.270 --> 01:00:51.230
with a pack of Marlboro Reds

961
01:00:52.357 --> 01:00:54.442
comes up to me and says.

962
01:00:54.525 --> 01:00:56.694
"What do you weigh?"

963
01:01:04.160 --> 01:01:05.662
And I lied.

964
01:01:05.745 --> 01:01:07.955
I lied.

965
01:01:10.958 --> 01:01:13.336
And I watched nine more people...

966
01:01:13.419 --> 01:01:16.422
He has nine more people.
and I watch them all lie.

967
01:01:18.424 --> 01:01:20.134
And I thought. "Oh my Lord."

968
01:01:20.635 --> 01:01:22.178
"We're gonna go down."

969
01:01:27.517 --> 01:01:30.061
We all get in this
tiny little float plane.

970
01:01:30.144 --> 01:01:33.064
and they put
these big old headphones on us.

971
01:01:33.147 --> 01:01:35.566
And somebody's narrating.
I think it's Wink Martindale.

972
01:01:39.362 --> 01:01:42.740
And all the sudden.
this little man starts pumping his foot.

973
01:01:43.491 --> 01:01:45.331
Pumping his foot.
that's how we get in the air.

974
01:01:45.368 --> 01:01:46.744
He's pumping that plane.

975
01:01:51.040 --> 01:01:54.585
I don't know if I saw a glacier.
I don't know if I saw one.

976
01:01:54.669 --> 01:01:56.796
One. because it was all white everywhere.

977
01:01:56.879 --> 01:01:58.131
but also. I was praying.

978
01:01:58.214 --> 01:01:59.424
I was praying.

979
01:01:59.507 --> 01:02:03.302
And I took my purse handles.
and took 'em around my neck.

980
01:02:03.970 --> 01:02:07.390
and put that purse on in case
somebody needed to identify my body.

981
01:02:15.648 --> 01:02:18.776
There was another time
that we went to Alaska.

982
01:02:18.860 --> 01:02:22.739
and my husband signed us up
for the largest zip line in North America.

983
01:02:23.823 --> 01:02:28.202
And we got on a rickety school bus
with a high school boy driving

984
01:02:28.286 --> 01:02:29.912
that was high on marijuana.

985
01:02:32.915 --> 01:02:35.376
And he drove us
up to the top of that mountain.

986
01:02:35.460 --> 01:02:38.296
And we all got out.
and he said. "Okay. listen.

987
01:02:38.379 --> 01:02:41.174
there's a couple of grizzlies
that live up here."

988
01:02:43.259 --> 01:02:45.678
"If they pop up out of that rock.
just run."

989
01:02:53.269 --> 01:02:55.730
All right. let me tell y'all
that being from Adams. Tennessee.

990
01:02:55.813 --> 01:02:56.939
we went on vacations.

991
01:02:57.023 --> 01:02:59.358
But my mom and dad had a farm.
they still have their farm.

992
01:02:59.442 --> 01:03:02.945
and they raised me and my sister.
put us through school.

993
01:03:03.029 --> 01:03:06.407
They had a meat processing plant.
and they did everybody's meat

994
01:03:06.491 --> 01:03:08.117
in Middle Tennessee and Kentucky.

995
01:03:08.785 --> 01:03:10.536
So they worked like Trojans.

996
01:03:10.620 --> 01:03:13.498
So we went on vacations. but it was...

997
01:03:13.581 --> 01:03:15.541
You know. we couldn't go far
most of the time.

998
01:03:15.625 --> 01:03:17.794
We'd go to Florida every once in a while.

999
01:03:17.877 --> 01:03:19.477
Most of the time. we'd go to Gatlinburg.

1000
01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:22.632
'cause my little daddy loves Gatlinburg.
and he still loves it.

1001
01:03:22.715 --> 01:03:24.967
And... I try to take him when I can.

1002
01:03:25.051 --> 01:03:28.387
And this is the one memory
they have of me growing up.

1003
01:03:28.471 --> 01:03:31.349
and they bring it up
every Thanksgiving and Christmas.

1004
01:03:32.517 --> 01:03:33.351
And they say.

1005
01:03:33.434 --> 01:03:36.038
"Remember when we were in Gatlinburg.
and Leanne was 18 months old.

1006
01:03:36.062 --> 01:03:37.855
and ate that cigarette butt
off the ground?"

1007
01:03:46.572 --> 01:03:50.201
And I think. "Is that the only thing
y'all remember about me?"

1008
01:03:51.994 --> 01:03:53.621
So I had never been

1009
01:03:53.704 --> 01:03:57.166
on these kind of trips
that I'm talking about. so...

1010
01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.502
Most of the time.
these trips are somewhere tropical.

1011
01:03:59.585 --> 01:04:00.670
and that's all wonderful.

1012
01:04:00.753 --> 01:04:03.339
And I don't mean to sound
that I'm not grateful for it. but...

1013
01:04:03.840 --> 01:04:07.009
that means that I've gotta go
and try on a bathing suit

1014
01:04:07.093 --> 01:04:08.719
in the dead of winter

1015
01:04:08.803 --> 01:04:11.347
before the end of January. early February.

1016
01:04:11.430 --> 01:04:12.890
and I'd rather take a bullet.

1017
01:04:15.518 --> 01:04:17.520
And I'm sure
there are some girls here tonight

1018
01:04:17.603 --> 01:04:20.565
that love to try on a bathing suit
in the dead of winter.

1019
01:04:20.648 --> 01:04:23.818
but us East Tennessee girls
like to eat pork sausage.

1020
01:04:28.990 --> 01:04:32.076
And I've been
prepping for this trip for 25 years.

1021
01:04:32.159 --> 01:04:34.495
and I think every year.
"I'm gonna do better."

1022
01:04:34.579 --> 01:04:37.748
"I'm gonna do better. I'm gonna tone.
I'm gonna do better."

1023
01:04:37.832 --> 01:04:38.666
"And I'm gonna..."

1024
01:04:38.749 --> 01:04:41.419
"I don't have to buy
a Miraclesuit this year."

1025
01:04:41.502 --> 01:04:42.587
"I won't have to buy

1026
01:04:42.670 --> 01:04:45.131
a one-piece bathing suit
with a girdle in it."

1027
01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:46.841
"No."

1028
01:04:46.924 --> 01:04:48.926
And don't ever buy a lavender one.

1029
01:04:49.010 --> 01:04:50.970
Okay.

1030
01:04:52.388 --> 01:04:55.808
I can't even think
about going on one of these trips

1031
01:04:55.892 --> 01:04:57.768
until I can get through Christmas.

1032
01:04:58.352 --> 01:05:01.772
And I don't mean to sound
like everything falls on me.

1033
01:05:03.149 --> 01:05:04.942
but everything falls on me.

1034
01:05:06.152 --> 01:05:10.489
I love my family.
but they don't do anything to help me.

1035
01:05:10.573 --> 01:05:13.784
I do all the decorating.
the cooking. the cleaning.

1036
01:05:13.868 --> 01:05:15.995
the wrapping. the shopping. all that.

1037
01:05:16.078 --> 01:05:19.665
Last year on December 24th.
my husband said to me.

1038
01:05:19.749 --> 01:05:21.208
"Can I help you do anything?"

1039
01:05:27.173 --> 01:05:29.300
And I said. "I'm gonna beat you to death."

1040
01:05:32.470 --> 01:05:35.723
And I can't think about this trip.
'cause I gotta get ready for Christmas.

1041
01:05:35.806 --> 01:05:39.352
And I get so torn up
that I wanna take to the bed.

1042
01:05:39.435 --> 01:05:42.146
I wanna take to the bed.
but I can't take to the bed.

1043
01:05:42.229 --> 01:05:44.857
'cause if I take to the bed.
nobody's gonna have Christmas.

1044
01:05:45.858 --> 01:05:51.238
And in my twisted mind. I think.
"Oh. I can lose 40 pounds in four weeks."

1045
01:05:55.076 --> 01:05:56.702
"Yeah. I'll be all right."

1046
01:05:56.786 --> 01:05:58.704
"I can just do Weight Watchers again."

1047
01:05:59.538 --> 01:06:02.416
Because that's been so successful for me.

1048
01:06:07.088 --> 01:06:08.714
I've done every diet in the world.

1049
01:06:08.798 --> 01:06:11.008
My mama. and my sister. and I

1050
01:06:11.092 --> 01:06:12.176
took Dexatrim.

1051
01:06:12.927 --> 01:06:15.388
When I was 17 years old...

1052
01:06:16.097 --> 01:06:17.390
I'm the youngest.

1053
01:06:17.473 --> 01:06:19.976
You could buy it everywhere.
Do y'all remember Dexatrim?

1054
01:06:20.059 --> 01:06:21.435
Yeah.

1055
01:06:21.519 --> 01:06:22.770
It was speed.

1056
01:06:26.649 --> 01:06:27.900
We took speed

1057
01:06:29.402 --> 01:06:30.486
as a family.

1058
01:06:37.702 --> 01:06:38.869
We would take Dexatrim.

1059
01:06:38.953 --> 01:06:41.163
and our heads would itch.
and we'd fight in the yard.

1060
01:06:46.043 --> 01:06:47.043
We did.

1061
01:06:54.510 --> 01:06:56.429
So. one day...

1062
01:06:57.179 --> 01:07:00.766
One day.
I was looking through my VHS tapes.

1063
01:07:00.850 --> 01:07:02.810
and I pop this VHS tape

1064
01:07:02.893 --> 01:07:07.606
into this old VHS tape player
that's in my children's playroom.

1065
01:07:07.690 --> 01:07:09.692
And I thought. "Who are those people?"

1066
01:07:11.736 --> 01:07:16.115
This was a VHS tape of me and my husband
on one of these trips

1067
01:07:16.198 --> 01:07:19.577
doing a snorkeling excursion in Maui.

1068
01:07:20.411 --> 01:07:22.747
And we had moved to San Antonio.

1069
01:07:22.830 --> 01:07:25.875
My husband had gotten a big promotion
to be over South Texas.

1070
01:07:25.958 --> 01:07:28.669
and he gives 150% at everything he does.

1071
01:07:28.753 --> 01:07:32.089
So he was torn up over that.
and trying to do the best he could.

1072
01:07:32.173 --> 01:07:35.134
And I'd moved these little children
from Tennessee to Texas.

1073
01:07:35.217 --> 01:07:36.135
and I was torn up.

1074
01:07:36.218 --> 01:07:38.137
And that was the first time
I got the shingles.

1075
01:07:39.013 --> 01:07:43.642
And instead of coping effectively.
and getting out and jogging.

1076
01:07:44.268 --> 01:07:45.895
we ate tortillas.

1077
01:07:48.564 --> 01:07:51.984
I pop this VHS tape in.
I thought. "Who are these people?"

1078
01:07:58.199 --> 01:08:02.078
It was me and my husband.
I did not recognize us.

1079
01:08:03.329 --> 01:08:04.830
We were so bloated

1080
01:08:06.624 --> 01:08:08.876
and pale from eating tortillas.

1081
01:08:08.959 --> 01:08:11.045
Our heads were this big.

1082
01:08:13.005 --> 01:08:15.508
You could not fit 'em in a bushel basket.

1083
01:08:17.468 --> 01:08:19.762
All right. so this whole VHS tape...

1084
01:08:19.845 --> 01:08:22.348
And I'll release it someday.
'cause let me tell you.

1085
01:08:22.431 --> 01:08:24.809
everybody on that boat
was from my husband's company.

1086
01:08:24.892 --> 01:08:27.937
except this honeymoon couple
down here on the right.

1087
01:08:28.020 --> 01:08:31.774
down right at the bottom.
and they were practically fornicating.

1088
01:08:34.443 --> 01:08:36.695
So I'll release it so y'all can watch.

1089
01:08:37.238 --> 01:08:38.238
Okay?

1090
01:08:39.990 --> 01:08:43.119
We get on this boat.
and I remember it like it was yesterday.

1091
01:08:43.202 --> 01:08:46.914
The first person that came to us
was this stunning woman.

1092
01:08:46.997 --> 01:08:50.584
I've never seen somebody
as pretty in a bikini in my life.

1093
01:08:50.668 --> 01:08:52.795
Beautiful. tan. blond.

1094
01:08:52.878 --> 01:08:55.548
She goes. "I'm gonna film all day."

1095
01:08:55.631 --> 01:08:58.717
"Do y'all want me to film y'all
on the boat and in the water?"

1096
01:08:58.801 --> 01:09:01.971
"And it's this amount of money."
And it was a lot. It was very expensive.

1097
01:09:02.054 --> 01:09:03.305
And I went. "Yes!"

1098
01:09:03.806 --> 01:09:05.808
And...

1099
01:09:06.767 --> 01:09:09.687
And my husband was like...
handing her a credit card.

1100
01:09:13.899 --> 01:09:16.318
And we got on this boat. and I don't...

1101
01:09:16.402 --> 01:09:19.613
You know. people were already partying.
and I don't like all that kind of stuff.

1102
01:09:19.697 --> 01:09:21.949
And I don't like to go out
in the middle of the ocean.

1103
01:09:22.032 --> 01:09:22.950
I was freaked out.

1104
01:09:23.033 --> 01:09:25.703
And so I remember
I had one of those patches on

1105
01:09:25.786 --> 01:09:27.538
that keeps you from vomiting

1106
01:09:27.621 --> 01:09:30.583
but it gives you double vision
at the same time.

1107
01:09:32.293 --> 01:09:34.753
And everybody's on that boat.
having a big time.

1108
01:09:34.837 --> 01:09:36.505
And somebody's cooking Chinese food.

1109
01:09:36.589 --> 01:09:39.842
and somebody's serving alcohol.
and everybody's having a big time.

1110
01:09:39.925 --> 01:09:42.678
And there's a man
that teaches you how to snorkel

1111
01:09:43.262 --> 01:09:44.638
on the way out there

1112
01:09:44.722 --> 01:09:45.848
in ten minutes.

1113
01:09:47.433 --> 01:09:49.894
And he gives us
all this snorkeling equipment.

1114
01:09:49.977 --> 01:09:51.812
And I've got. you know. all this on.

1115
01:09:51.896 --> 01:09:54.982
He puts a big.
old floater thing on me with a strap.

1116
01:09:55.733 --> 01:09:57.610
and throws me into the ocean.

1117
01:09:59.195 --> 01:10:01.155
And I feel something.

1118
01:10:01.238 --> 01:10:02.364
"Is that an eel?"

1119
01:10:05.075 --> 01:10:06.452
"Is that an eel?"

1120
01:10:08.412 --> 01:10:10.956
And then my husband floats up to me.

1121
01:10:11.040 --> 01:10:14.710
He's got on a big pair of goggles
and a big thing in his mouth.

1122
01:10:15.252 --> 01:10:18.088
Takes that thing out.
and looks at me. and says.

1123
01:10:18.589 --> 01:10:19.590
"You want to do it?"

1124
01:10:31.060 --> 01:10:32.394
And I said.

1125
01:10:32.478 --> 01:10:33.771
"Get away from me!"

1126
01:10:37.816 --> 01:10:40.277
And through this whole VHS tape...

1127
01:10:41.528 --> 01:10:43.906
But I remember it like it was yesterday.

1128
01:10:43.989 --> 01:10:45.616
He is twirling.

1129
01:10:47.284 --> 01:10:48.369
And diving.

1130
01:10:51.163 --> 01:10:52.164
Twirling.

1131
01:10:52.665 --> 01:10:54.375
diving. and doing all this.

1132
01:10:54.458 --> 01:10:57.795
And the first thing I thought...
My heart dropped when I thought.

1133
01:10:58.337 --> 01:10:59.672
"Is he showing off

1134
01:11:00.881 --> 01:11:02.967
in front of this woman in the bikini?"

1135
01:11:03.676 --> 01:11:06.303
"Is he having unbiblical thoughts

1136
01:11:07.137 --> 01:11:08.138
about her?"

1137
01:11:08.806 --> 01:11:10.182
Then I took a beat and I thought.

1138
01:11:10.266 --> 01:11:12.186
"No. that's not who he is.
That's not who he is."

1139
01:11:12.226 --> 01:11:13.786
And I thought. "Oh. I know what it is."

1140
01:11:13.852 --> 01:11:16.397
"He doesn't like to spend money.
This is costing a lot."

1141
01:11:16.480 --> 01:11:19.483
I know in his mind. he thought.
"I'm gonna freaking twirl."

1142
01:11:21.944 --> 01:11:26.532
So he's twirling. and doing.
and doing. and doing.

1143
01:11:27.324 --> 01:11:31.370
He had been
taking Propecia for about a year.

1144
01:11:31.453 --> 01:11:33.414
to grow this one patch of hair out.

1145
01:11:36.542 --> 01:11:39.670
And Propecia works. let me tell you.
It works.

1146
01:11:39.753 --> 01:11:43.340
Through this whole VHS tape.
this one patch of hair.

1147
01:11:53.767 --> 01:11:57.688
And then all of the sudden.
this big. lavender thing...

1148
01:12:13.370 --> 01:12:15.205
...comes across the screen.

1149
01:12:16.206 --> 01:12:18.042
And I think. "What is that?"

1150
01:12:20.127 --> 01:12:21.378
"Is that a turtle?"

1151
01:12:22.880 --> 01:12:25.716
Thank y'all! Thank y'all!

1152
01:12:25.799 --> 01:12:29.011
Thank y'all!

1153
01:12:31.513 --> 01:12:33.599
I'm gonna bring out my family!

